	<description>
	<overview>Use the <b>padding</b> property to add padding to table cells.</overview>

		<parameters>
  <parameter>
    <name>pixels</name>
    <description>The number of pixels to add as padding around the contents of the cells in a table.</description>
  </parameter>		</parameters>

	<value>The <b>padding</b> of a line or field returns the padding size as a number.</value>
	<comments>The <b>padding</b> property adds padding to all sides of a table cell. The padding property only has an effect on a table in a field.<p></p><p>To create a table within a field use the <property tag="tabStops">tabStops</property> property.</p></comments>
	</description>
